********** README for using CMU's scenario and connction pattern  *****
            ************** file generator ************

A.scenario file generator
---------------------------
Files:
Makefile
setdest.h setdest.cc
make-scen.csh


Steps for creating scenario files for mobility simulations :

* compile to create an executable setdest.

* run setdest with arguments in the following way:
./setdest -n <num_of_nodes> -p <pausetime> -s <maxspeed> -t <simtime> \
      -x <maxx> -y <maxy> > <outdir>/<scenario-file>

* OR run make-scen.csh to generate multiple scenario files.


B. Connection pattern file generator
-------------------------------------

Files:
cbrgen.tcl -- for generating CBR connections
tcpgen.tcl -- for generating TCP connections

Method:

to create CBR connecions, run

ns cbrgen.tcl [-type cbr|tcp] [-nn nodes] [-seed seed] [-mc connections]
[-rate rate]

and to create TCP connections, run

ns tcpgen.tcl [-nn nodes] [-seed seed]

note: You will need to pipe the outputs from above to a cbr-* or a tcp-*
file. 
